briefdescription.para: Create a new hashmap with standard kernel allocators.

User data passed to compare (and may be used internally).

briefdescription.para: Clear all items from the map.

detaileddescription.para: Each element is passed to elfree (if provided). If update_cap is true, internal capacity is trimmed to the current number of buckets to avoid new allocations on the clear.

parameterdescription.para: When true, shrink capacity to current bucket count.

detaileddescription.para:
map
Hashmap handle.
item
Item to insert (by value).
Pointer to the replaced item if it existed, otherwise NULL.
On allocation failure returns NULL and sets the sticky OOM flag (see hashmap_oom).

briefdescription.para: Look up an item by key.

simplesect.para: Pointer to stored item, or NULL if not found.

parameterdescription.para: Bucket index (will be reduced modulo bucket count).

simplesect.para: Pointer to stored item at that bucket, or NULL.
Pointer to the removed item, or NULL if not found.

briefdescription.para: Get the number of stored items.
Free a hashmap and its storage.

detaileddescription.para: Calls elfree for each element if provided, then releases internal buffers via the map’s allocator callbacks.

briefdescription.para: Test whether the previous hashmap_set failed due to OOM.

simplesect.para: true if the last set operation ran out of memory.

briefdescription.para: Iterate over every item in the map.

parameterdescription.para: Callback invoked for each item; return false to stop early.

simplesect.para: false if iteration was stopped early, true otherwise.

detaileddescription.para:
map
Hashmap handle.
i
Cursor (initialise to 0; updated on each call).
item
Out: pointer to the current stored item.
true if an item was produced; false if iteration is complete.
Note: If hashmap_delete is called during iteration, the bucket layout may change. Reset the cursor to 0 to restart iteration safely.

briefdescription.para: Open-addressed hashmap (Robin Hood), with allocator udata support.

detaileddescription.para: Updated by Craig Edwards, September 2025, to allow udata to be passed to the allocator functions. This enables contextual/arena allocators (e.g., per BASIC interpreter context) without altering external call sites.
